  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6778.25 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6783 and beneath the massive +28.6B gamma wall at 6780, dealers are currently positioned to sell any push higher into that resistance zone while providing buying support above the -15.6B negative gamma pocket at 6770. The PIN regime with nearly 100B in total GEX creates a tight range-bound environment where dealers will aggressively fade moves away from the 6775-6780 zone. The recent GEX surge (169.5% over 5min) indicates heavy options flow that's further cementing dealer positioning to defend these levels.\n\nKey levels: 6770 (dealer buying kicks in below), 6780 (heavy dealer selling), and 6783 GEX flip as the pivot point for regime change.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 6770-6780 with dealers capping upside moves.",
